A New York-based Investment Funds Attorney, Femi Gbede, has partnered with Africa Health Holdings Limited (“AHH”) in his scholarship programme for 2022. This partnership adds to what is already a mouth-watering scholarship opportunity for law graduates preparing to attend the Nigerian Law School, as AHH, an investment management company, will provide summer internship opportunities to two of Femi Gbede’s scholars, as well as NYSC placements. In a post on his LinkedIn page, Gbede explained that there will be two application cycles per year due to the new collaboration with AHH. ICYMI: FCTA refutes ordering principals to contribute N20,000 for release of kidnapped UBEB boss According to him, “Consistent with my practice since 2017, I am happy to announce that the early cycle application for the Femi Gbede Scholarship is now open. “Going forward, there will be two application cycles per year so the scholars can benefit from a new collaboration I forged with Africa Health Holdings Limited (AHH) (with offices in New York, Lagos, Accra and Nairobi). “This will give summer internships to two successful candidates, with additional NYSC opportunities (also open to successful candidates from the regular application cycle). “Additional scholarships will be available during the regular application cycle later in the year. “Many thanks to Africa Health Holdings Limited (AHH) for adding value by providing these summer internship and NYSC opportunities to the scholars.” Eight (8) beneficiaries of Femi Gbede scholarship are currently studying at various campuses of the Nigerian Law School.    NIGERIAN TRIBUNE